casebody.data:
HENRY WHEELER, Receiver, &c., Plaintiff and Appellant, v. JEROME E. BATES et al., Defendants and Respondents.

Before Freedman, Van Vorst and Speir, JJ.

Decided December 9, 1874. Titus B. Eldridge, for appellant. P. & D. Mitchell, for respondents.

Appeal from an order denying motion for judgment for want of an answer, and from order opening default and permitting defendant to answer. Orders affirmed.

No opinion.
